title: Report unlicensed taxis, minicabs or private hire vehicles

heading_context: Report unlicensed taxis, minicabs or private hire vehicles
chunks.html_content:
Taxis and private hire vehicles (also called minicabs) must have a licence from the local council or Transport for London (TfL).

Report a vehicle, driver or operator that’s unlicensed by either:

  • contacting the local council where you saw them
  • contacting TfL if you saw them in London

heading_context: Report unlicensed taxis, minicabs or private hire vehicles
Check if a vehicle is licensed correctly
chunks.html_content:
A private hire vehicle (PHV) can only be pre-booked. Taxis can also be hailed in the street or hired at a rank in the area they’re licensed by.

Taxis have a plate on the back showing their taxi licence number and the area they’re licensed by.

They usually have a ‘TAXI’ roof sign.

Taxis can only be hailed in the area they’re licensed by, but they can be pre-booked from anywhere.

heading_context: Report unlicensed taxis, minicabs or private hire vehicles
Check if a vehicle is licensed correctly
chunks.html_content:
To show they’re licensed, most PHVs must display either a:

  • special licence plate on the front or rear of the vehicle
  • special disc on the windscreen or rear window

Some PHVs are exempt, such as executive hire vehicles.
